#  One may use this script to execute information and complexity only for few diatomic molecules (As an example {B3LYP,6-311G**} basis and functional are included for test run). 
# Needed Input files :: 1) cmatup.dat 
#                       2) cmatdw.dat      !! FOR UHF CALCULATION BOTH FILES ARE NEASSERY.BUT FOR RHF  
#                                          !! ONE MAY USE ONLY ONE OF THEM.BUT ANOTHER FILE SHOULD BE EXSIST IN THE SOURCE CODE DIRECTORY FOR SMOOTH RUN.  
#
#                       3)geo.dat
#                       4)lmn.dat
#                       5)alpha_beta_method.dat
#                       6)noa_npg_noc_norb.dat
#                       7)grid_point.dat
#                       8)atomic_number.dat
#                       9)npg1.dat
#                      10)exponent.dat
#                      11)precoef.dat
#                      12)npg1.dat                      

#  One can easly generate those input files by executing " g++ DRIVER.C -o input_script 
#                                                          ./input_script".                        
# But I recommend you for this, use 'Input_tool' Directory.

# As a output you will get complexity.dat, information.dat and Moments.dat files. 
# For 5 to 9 you have to put explicite values. For noc and npg you may see 'npgnoc', which will be appear in 'Input_tool' Directory.

